  <section id="about">
    <h2>About this app</h2>
    <p>
      Family Calendar is a small, family-shared calendar app. Registered users can create
      events directly in the app and connect a Google Calendar (and, in future versions,
      Zoho Calendar) so that events sync between Family Calendar and the user's existing
      calendar accounts. An admin-curated daily feed (weather, bills, local events,
      thoughts, and jokes) supplements the calendar view.
    </p>
    <p>
      Family Calendar is a product of madLadsLab. Other madLadsLab products include
      <a href="https://slab.madladslab.com">Slab</a>, <a href="https://towers.madladslab.com">Towers</a>,
      and others listed at <a href="https://madladslab.com">madladslab.com</a>.
      Each product is operated as a separate application; this Privacy Policy applies
      specifically to <code>family-calendar.madladslab.com</code>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="privacy">
    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>

    <h3>What we collect</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account profile</strong> from Google sign-in: your email, display name, and Google account ID.</li>
      <li><strong>Calendar data</strong> you authorize us to read or write — events on your primary Google Calendar, including titles, times, locations, descriptions, and attendee email addresses where present.</li>
      <li><strong>OAuth refresh token</strong> issued by Google. Stored encrypted at rest using AES-256-GCM with a key held only on the application server.</li>
      <li><strong>Events you create in Family Calendar</strong> directly.</li>
      <li><strong>Server logs</strong> covering request paths, timestamps, response codes, and IP addresses, retained for routine operation and security review.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What we do with it</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Display your calendar in the Family Calendar UI alongside other family members.</li>
      <li>Sync events you create in Family Calendar back to your Google Calendar, and pull events from Google Calendar into Family Calendar.</li>
      <li>Render the daily admin-curated feed (weather, bills, local events, thoughts, jokes) for your family.</li>
      <li>Provide an authenticated outbound API to other madLadsLab products (e.g. Slab tenant admin panels) <em>only</em> when you have explicitly issued an API key for that purpose from the admin panel.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What we do not do</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third-party advertisers.</li>
      <li>We do not use your calendar data to train or personalize machine-learning models.</li>
      <li>We do not transfer your data to other madLadsLab products without an explicit, revocable API key issued by you.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Where it lives</h3>
    <p>
      All application data is stored in MongoDB Atlas in the United States. OAuth refresh
      tokens are encrypted at rest before being written. Static assets (if any) are served
      from Linode Object Storage.
    </p>

    <h3>How long we keep it</h3>
    <p>
      Account and calendar data are retained for as long as your account is active. You can
      delete your account at any time by emailing us (see Contact below); upon deletion we
      will revoke OAuth refresh tokens, delete calendar events, and delete account records
      within 30 days. Server logs are kept for up to 90 days.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="google">
    <h2>Google User Data</h2>
    <p>
      Family Calendar's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs adheres
      to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>,
      including the Limited Use requirements.
    </p>

    <h3>Scopes we request</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>profile</code> — your basic profile (name, picture).</li>
      <li><code>email</code> — your primary email address, used as your account identifier.</li>
      <li><code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar</code> — read and write events on the calendars you own.</li>
      <li><code>https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar.events</code> — read and write individual events.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Revoking access</h3>
    <p>
      You can revoke Family Calendar's access to your Google account at any time at
      <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions">myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>.
      When access is revoked, scheduled syncs from your Google Calendar will stop on the
      next attempt, and you can additionally email us to request deletion of any data we
      have already pulled.
    </p>
  </section>

